# Dynamic Content Test

This page tests variables, calculations, and conditionals working inside `<<onclick>>` and `<<delayed>>` macros.

---

## Test 1: Variables in Onclick

Click below to set a variable dynamically:

<<onclick text="Click to set variable">>
<<var:clickedOnce type="boolean">>true<</var>>
<<var:clickTime type="number">><<calc>>Date.now()<</calc>><</var>>

✅ Variable set! `clickedOnce` is now: ${clickedOnce}
Line breaks work correctly!  
Each line appears on its own line.  
<</onclick>>

---

## Test 2: Conditionals in Onclick

<<var:playerScore type="number">>50<</var>>

Your score: **${playerScore}**

<<onclick text="Check your score">>
<<var:playerScore type="number">>150<</var>>

Score updated to: **${playerScore}**

<<if:playerScore at least 100>>
🎉 Congratulations! You passed the threshold!
<</if>>

<<if:playerScore less than 100>>
⚠️ Keep trying to reach 100 points.
<</if>>
<</onclick>>

---

## Test 3: Calculations in Onclick

<<var:counter type="number">>0<</var>>

Counter: **${counter}**

<<onclick text="Increment Counter">>
<<var:counter type="number">><<calc>>${counter} + 1<</calc>><</var>>

Counter is now: **${counter}**

<<if:counter at least 3>>
🏆 You've clicked 3 or more times!
<</if>>
<</onclick>>

---

## Test 4: Variables in Delayed

After 2 seconds, a variable will be set:

<<delayed time="2000">>
<<var:delayedVar>>This was set after 2 seconds<</var>>

✨ Delayed variable set: ${delayedVar}
<</delayed>>

---

## Test 5: Line Breaks in Onclick

Testing that line breaks are preserved properly:

<<onclick text="Show multi-line content">>
Line 1: First line of content   S
Line 2: Second line of content   
Line 3: Third line of content   

Empty line above!    
**Bold text** on this line    
*Italic text* on this line    
<</onclick>>

---

## Test 6: Complex Example

<<var:health type="number">>75<</var>>
<<var:hasPotion type="boolean">>true<</var>>

**Health:** ${health} HP  
**Has Potion:** ${hasPotion}

<<onclick text="Use Potion">>
<<var:hasPotion type="boolean">>false<</var>>
<<var:health type="number">><<calc>>${health} + 25<</calc>><</var>>

💊 Potion used!

**New Health:** ${health} HP

<<if:health at least 100>>
💚 You're at full health!
<</if>>

<<if:hasPotion is false>>
⚠️ You've used your only potion.
<</if>>
<</onclick>>

---

All of these now work because the content is processed **dynamically** when revealed, not pre-rendered!

